                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Fol. 1a: The book Gorgorios (Zagorgorios Nabiye). The text has been published by Joseph Halevy in his book Teezaza Sanbat together with a French translation. Our manuscript shows numerous variant readings, omissions and additions as compared with Halevy's text -- 21a: The death of Moses (Mota Muse). This text has been published by Dr. J. Faitlovitch in 1906 together with a translation -- 31a: A prayer enumerating the different Divine Names. To each of them is attributed one of the Biblical miracles --
                            35a: Various Falasha prayers and Hymns. Identical with the prayers contained in manuscript no.17, but as usual with many variants -- 76a: A short Biblical history -- 78b: A prayer for mercy. Unfinished. The last lines illegible</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1r">Fols 1r and following</locus>
                            <title>The book Gorgorios (Zagorgorios Nabiye)</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note>The text has been published by Joseph Halevy in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/WNVWEBVV"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Halevy1902Sanbat"/><title level="m">Těʾězâza sanbat (commandements du Sabbat), accompagné de six autres écrits pseudo-épigraphiques admis par les Falachas ou Juifs d'Abyssinie: Texte éthiopien</title><title level="s">Bibliothèque de l'École des Hautes Études, Sciences historiques et philologiques</title><author><forename>Joseph</forename><surname>Halévy</surname></author><editor><forename>Joseph</forename><surname>Halévy</surname></editor><pubPlace>Paris</pubPlace><publisher>Librairie Émile Bouillon, éditeur</publisher><date>1902</date><series><title level="s">Bibliothèque de l'École des Hautes Études, Sciences historiques et philologiques</title><biblScope unit="volume">137</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">137</biblScope><note type="url">http://menadoc.bibliothek.uni-halle.de/ssg/content/titleinfo/530053</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Halevy1902Sanbat</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Halevy1902Sanbat</note></bibl> together with a French translation. Our manuscript shows numerous variant readings, omissions and additions as compared with Halevy's text</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="21r">Fols 21r and following</locus>
                            <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2024MotaMu">The death of Moses (Mota Muse)</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>                            
                          
                            <note>This text has been published by Dr. J. Faitlovitch in 1906 together with a translation</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="31r">Fols 31r and following</locus>
                            <title>A prayer enumerating the different Divine Names</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note>To each name is attributed one of the Biblical miracles</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <locus from="35r">Fols 35r and following</locus>
                            <title>Beta ʾƎsrāʾel prayers and hymns</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note>Identical with the prayers contained in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/TAfait017">manuscript no.17</ref>, but as usual with many variants</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                            <locus from="76r">Fols 76r and following</locus>
                            <title>A short Biblical history</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                            <locus from="78v">Fols 78v and following</locus>
                            <title type="incomplete">A prayer for mercy</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note>Unfinished. The last lines illegible</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
